<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900702-0025</DOCNO><DOCID>900702-0025.</DOCID><HL>   Tesoro to Pay Trinidad   $2.8 Million to Settle Suit</HL><DATE>07/02/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LATAM TSO</CO><LP>   SAN ANTONIO, Texas -- Tesoro Petroleum Corp. said it willpay the government of Trinidad and Tobago $2.8 million tosettle litigation related to a now-defunct oil explorationand production venture.   The Trinidad and Tobago government, in a lawsuit filedlast year, sought unspecified damages and the return of $350million in profits it said were generated by the jointventure. Trinidad-Tobago accused Tesoro of wire and mailfraud, racketeering, bribery and violations of prostitutionlaws.</LP><TEXT>   &quot;Tesoro has always been confident it would prevail in atrial . . . and still maintains that conviction,&quot; therefining and marketing concern said. &quot;Nonetheless, thecompany has elected to settle on what it regards as veryfavorable terms compared to the cost of extended litigation.&quot;   Officials of Trinidad-Tobago hailed the settlement as avictory. Prime Minister A.N.R. Robinson said, &quot;The case andits settlement show that corruption is wrong and the peopleof Trinidad and Tobago will tolerate it no longer.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>